briefTitle: A Study of an Ad26.RSV.PreF-based Regimen at the End of Shelf-life in Adults Aged 60 to 75 Years
officialTitle: A Randomized, Double-blind Phase 3 Study to Assess the Immunogenicity and Safety of an Ad26.RSV.PreF-based Regimen at the End of Shelf-life in Adults Aged 60 to 75 Years
summary: The purpose of this study is to demonstrate non-inferiority in terms of humoral immune responses of Ad26.RSV.preF-based study vaccine lots representative of different aged vaccine in comparison to a non-aged Ad26.RSV.preF-based study vaccine lot.

primaryOutcome.measure: Geometric Mean Titers (GMTs) of Prefusion F-protein (preF) Antibodies as Assessed by Enzyme-linked Immunosorbent Assay (ELISA) 14 Days Post Vaccination

effectByArm.arm: Group 1: Ad26.RSV.preF 1.0*10^11 vp + RSV preF Protein 150 mcg
Group 2: Ad26.RSV.preF 2.5*10^10 vp + RSV preF Protein 150 mcg
Group 3: Ad26.RSV.preF 1.0*10^10 vp + RSV preF Protein 150 mcg
